{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit"]]},"sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"text":"Overview","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"TUIkit offers two ways to create custom views:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"header":"row","type":"table","rows":[[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Approach"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"When to Use","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Complexity"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Composite View"}]},{"type":"text","text":" ("},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/View","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"body"},{"type":"text","text":")"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Combining existing views into reusable components"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Low"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"View Modifier","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" ("},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/ViewModifier"},{"type":"text","text":")"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Transforming any view’s rendered buffer (padding, background)"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Medium"}],"type":"paragraph"}]]]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Most custom views should be "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"composite views","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":". For buffer-level transformations, implement a custom "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/ViewModifier","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Composite Views","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Composite-Views"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A composite view implements the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"body"},{"type":"text","text":" property to compose existing views. This is the same pattern as SwiftUI:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["struct StatusHeader: View {","    let title: String","    let version: String","","    var body: some View {","        VStack {","            HStack {","                Text(title)","                    .bold()","                    .foregroundColor(.palette.accent)","                Spacer()","                Text(\"v\\(version)\")","                    .foregroundColor(.palette.foregroundTertiary)","            }","            Divider()","        }","    }","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"body"},{"text":" property is annotated with ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@ViewBuilder"},{"text":" at the protocol level, so you can use all result builder features: conditionals, optionals, loops:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["struct UserCard: View {","    let name: String","    let role: String?","","    var body: some View {","        Panel(title: name) {","            Text(name).bold()","            if let role {","                Text(role)","                    .foregroundColor(.palette.foregroundSecondary)","                    .italic()","            }","        }","    }","}"]},{"text":"Accepting Child Content","level":3,"type":"heading","anchor":"Accepting-Child-Content"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To create container-style views that accept child content, use a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@ViewBuilder"},{"type":"text","text":" closure parameter:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["struct Section<Content: View>: View {","    let title: String","    let content: Content","","    init(title: String, @ViewBuilder content: () -> Content) {","        self.title = title","        self.content = content()","    }","","    var body: some View {","        VStack(alignment: .leading) {","            Text(title)","                .bold()","                .underline()","            content","        }","    }","}","","\/\/ Usage","Section(title: \"Settings\") {","    Text(\"Option A\")","    Text(\"Option B\")","}"]},{"text":"Building Custom Containers","level":3,"type":"heading","anchor":"Building-Custom-Containers"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For richer containers, compose existing container views like "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/Panel","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/Card","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"code":"Box","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", or "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/Dialog","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":":"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["struct SettingsGroup<Content: View>: View {","    let title: String","    let content: Content","","    init(_ title: String, @ViewBuilder content: () -> Content) {","        self.title = title","        self.content = content()","    }","","    var body: some View {","        Panel(title, borderStyle: .rounded, titleColor: .palette.accent) {","            content","        }","    }","}","","\/\/ Usage","SettingsGroup(\"Network\") {","    Text(\"Proxy: none\")","    Text(\"DNS: auto\")","}"]},{"text":"View Modifiers","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"View-Modifiers"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/ViewModifier"},{"type":"text","text":" transforms an already-rendered "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/FrameBuffer"},{"type":"text","text":". Use this when your transformation operates on the output of any view:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["struct HighlightModifier: ViewModifier {","    let color: Color","","    func modify(buffer: FrameBuffer, context: RenderContext) -> FrameBuffer {","        \/\/ Transform each line in the buffer","        var result = FrameBuffer()","        for line in buffer.lines {","            result.appendLine(ANSIRenderer.applyPersistentBackground(to: line, color: color))","        }","        return result","    }","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Apply it using ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".modifier(_:)"},{"text":":","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["Text(\"Important!\")","    .modifier(HighlightModifier(color: .red))"]},{"text":"Convenience Extensions","level":3,"type":"heading","anchor":"Convenience-Extensions"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For a cleaner API, add a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"View"},{"type":"text","text":" extension:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["extension View {","    func highlighted(_ color: Color = .red) -> some View {","        modifier(HighlightModifier(color: color))","    }","}","","\/\/ Usage","Text(\"Important!\").highlighted(.yellow)"]},{"text":"When to Use ViewModifier","level":3,"type":"heading","anchor":"When-to-Use-ViewModifier"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Use ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/ViewModifier","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" when your transformation is a pure buffer-to-buffer operation: adding visual effects, changing backgrounds, or adjusting layout after rendering. The ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/RenderContext","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" gives you access to:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"header":